text.__SUMMARY__: Acer tutcheri (Tutcher's maple) is a species of deciduous maple tree native to the Fujian, Guangdong, Guangxi, south Hunan, south Jiangxi, Taiwan and south Zhejiang provinces of southern China including certain districts of Hong Kong.Acer tutcheri is found in forests between 300 and 1000 metres of altitude. It is a tree up to 15 metres tall, with brown bark. The leaves are up to 9 cm long and 13 cm across, with three or occasionally five lobes. They are deciduous, hairless, thin and papery, and have teeth along the edges.
